deno.lock
  info [lockfile-old-version] deno.lock is lockfile version 4 (the "version" field in that file). The current version of Deno writes version 5 and migrates old lockfiles automatically the next time the lockfile is written.
    fix: rewrite the lockfile at version 5 using the same migration Deno applies automatically on the next lockfile write

Deno 3 heads-up (report only, no fixes available yet):
  - Deno 3 changes some permission prompting defaults. There is no configuration to pin the current behavior yet; check the migration guide once available (https://docs.deno.com/runtime/help/deno-3).
  - Deno 3 changes how package-lock.json files are taken into account in npm-compatible projects. There is no configuration to pin the current behavior yet; check the migration guide once available (https://docs.deno.com/runtime/help/deno-3).

Found 1 finding (1 fixable with deno doctor --fix).
